    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the complete implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Stepper Compound Component\n\n**4 changes — 2 new files + 2 registry edits.**\n\n### Architecture\nTwo nested React contexts (mirrors `carousel.tsx`):\n- **`StepperContext`** (root): shares `activeStep` + `orientation` with all descendants\n- **`StepperItemContext`** (per-item): exposes `step` + derived `state` (`\"active\" | \"completed\" | \"pending\"`)\n\n`StepperContent` is a special case — it has its own `step` prop and only reads `activeStep` from root context, so it can live anywhere inside `<Stepper>` (not required to be inside `<StepperItem>`).\n\n### New Files\n\n**`ui/stepper.tsx`** — 7 named exports following all conventions (`\"use client\"`, `data-slot`, `cn()`, function declarations):\n- `Stepper` — root flex container + context provider\n- `StepperItem` — per-step wrapper with nested context, sets `data-state`/`data-step`\n- `StepperTrigger` — circle button (shows step number by default, or custom `children`)\n- `StepperTitle` / `StepperDescription` — text with state-based color\n- `StepperSeparator` — fills with `bg-primary` when `activeStep > step`\n- `StepperContent` — renders `null` (not hidden) when `step !== activeStep`\n\n**`examples/stepper-demo.tsx`** — 3-step \"Account / Profile / Complete\" demo using two `<Stepper>` instances (same `activeStep` state): one for the horizontal indicator row, one (flex-col override) for content panels. Plain `<button>` elements for navigation to keep registry deps as `[\"stepper\"]` only.\n\n### Registry Edits\n- **`ui/_registry.ts`**: Insert `stepper` entry (no npm deps) alphabetically between `spinner` and `switch`\n- **`examples/_registry.ts`**: Insert `stepper-demo` with `registryDependencies: [\"stepper\"]` after spinner entries",
